Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.30,0:00:21.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.76,0:00:24.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.59,0:00:26.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like the\NAldnoah drive shut down.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.10,0:00:28.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That shouldn't be possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.81,0:00:31.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This ship's Aldnoah was\Nactivated by Her Highness!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.81,0:00:36.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So long as she lives, it can't be shut down\Nby another without her consent!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.48,0:00:40.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So long as she lives...\NWhere is Seylum?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.28,0:00:43.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Where is she?\NWhere is Seylum?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.62,0:02:16.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damage?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.50,0:02:20.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damage to hull, negligible. Departmental\Ndamage checks underway.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.00,0:02:22.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We are currently operating\Non auxiliary power.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.75,0:02:24.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's a good thing we were\Nflying at low altitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.67,0:02:26.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Our gravity field was\Nchurning up the snow,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.34,0:02:28.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and that seems to have acted\Nas a shock absorber.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.09,0:02:30.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Launch our Kats\Nand put them on watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.76,0:02:33.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Repair any damaged areas ASAP.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.10,0:02:37.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Engine room, inspect the Aldnoah drive and\Ndetermine cause of shutdown.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.48,0:02:38.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Where is Capt. Magbaredge?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.56,0:02:42.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.82,0:02:44.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Send medics immediately!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.78,0:02:46.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Captain? Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.57,0:02:53.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Breathing and pulse, both stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.37,0:02:54.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Princess...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.36,0:02:55.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Bring towels!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.33,0:02:59.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to use a defibrillator.\NWe have to dry her off!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.21,0:03:00.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.25,0:03:01.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.79,0:03:02.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll help.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.34,0:03:10.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Setting counter shock\Nto 200 joules.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.51,0:03:13.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.18,0:03:18.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.73,0:03:20.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, you're too light.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.77,0:03:25.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You think fast on your feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.59,0:03:27.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We learn this in school.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.74,0:03:31.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Students never take it seriously. All they\Ndo is giggle about the mouth-to-mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.87,0:03:33.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It could save a life.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.72,0:03:51.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Should I take over?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.23,0:03:52.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.60,0:04:03.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milady!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.44,0:04:12.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Good. Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.20,0:04:14.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Inaho...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.91,0:04:17.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.29,0:04:20.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like you passed out while\Ntaking a shower. What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.87,0:04:23.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.84,0:04:28.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was attacked... by her!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.97,0:04:32.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't move.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.26,0:04:33.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.64,0:04:39.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rayet? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.73,0:04:41.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the patient?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.81,0:04:43.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stay back!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.48,0:04:45.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Get back!\NGet out of the room!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.19,0:04:47.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.82,0:04:52.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Yagarai.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.69,0:04:53.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.07,0:04:57.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.87,0:05:02.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A Versian- No, a Martian.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.75,0:05:09.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.17,0:05:14.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The one who tried to assassinate you\Nat the Shinawara parade
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.63,0:05:16.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,was my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.22,0:05:21.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He was a Martian spy living on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.52,0:05:25.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He was promised a title and\Na reward if he killed you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.52,0:05:29.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But when he completed his mission,\Nhe was put down like a dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.32,0:05:31.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To silence him!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.95,0:05:38.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Martians can't be trusted!\NMartians are all the enemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.16,0:05:45.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't go back to being a Martian.\NBut I'm not a Terran, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.25,0:05:50.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But you... you revealed\Nyourself as a Martian!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.80,0:05:55.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In spite of that, you were accepted! In spite\Nof that, you made a place for yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.72,0:05:57.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In spite of what you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.47,0:06:02.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He thought they were\Non the same side, but they...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.77,0:06:05.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's all your fault...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.98,0:06:08.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My father is dead\Nbecause you came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.02,0:06:11.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This war started\Nbecause you came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.03,0:06:15.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We were betrayed\Nbecause you came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.53,0:06:19.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm all alone\Nbecause you came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.20,0:06:23.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because you came...\NBecause you came...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.87,0:06:25.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because you came!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.12,0:06:29.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In spite of all that,\Nhow can they not hate you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.88,0:06:34.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.30,0:06:40.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've brought you nothing\Nbut misery, haven't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.68,0:06:45.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was a fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.85,0:06:46.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milady!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.69,0:06:51.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I was working\Ntowards peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.90,0:06:55.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I was doing\Nthe right thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.49,0:07:00.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I was merely acting\Nlike a spoiled child.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.66,0:07:04.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Relations with Earth are worse\Nthan ever because of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.46,0:07:10.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Many people have\Nlost their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.25,0:07:17.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how much I tell myself that\NI did nothing wrong, the reality of it
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.42,0:07:21.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,is that I have brought misery\Nto countless people's lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.72,0:07:26.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To yours.\NTo your father's.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.52,0:07:31.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will not ask you to forgive me.\NNevertheless... I am sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.48,0:07:36.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.23,0:07:38.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you crying?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.15,0:07:42.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My father tried to kill you!\NI tried to kill you, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.03,0:07:46.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why won't you hate me?!\NWhy are you forgiving me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.41,0:07:48.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you\Nbeing kind to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.62,0:07:52.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why?! Why?! Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.25,0:07:56.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.80,0:08:05.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How stupid are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.01,0:08:08.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Give it a rest, already...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.73,0:08:13.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What am I even doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.77,0:08:14.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.90,0:08:20.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.45,0:08:23.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Automatics won't fire\Nwith the slide open.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.41,0:08:27.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought this was the best way to stop\Nyou without it discharging accidentally.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.91,0:08:28.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, I meant-
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.95,0:08:33.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, I couldn't care less\Nif you're a Terran or a Martian.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.09,0:08:42.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You hate our enemies, and those\Nenemies are trying to kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.09,0:08:45.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But most importantly,\Nyou've fought at our side.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.26,0:08:48.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What other reasons\Ndo I need?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.02,0:08:50.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You trust me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.10,0:08:53.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At the very least, I don't\Nthink we're enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.90,0:08:57.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As to whether we'll be allies...\Nthat's up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.02,0:08:59.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You might come to regret this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.41,0:09:14.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm taking you into custody.\NWarrant Officer Kaizuka.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.67,0:09:15.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.04,0:09:17.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do whatever you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.84,0:09:29.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?\NA Martian trinket?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.60,0:09:32.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm told that it's a\NTerran good luck charm.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.73,0:09:36.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Yagarai, what's the\Nprincess' condition?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.31,0:09:41.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She seems fine. But to be safe,\Nshe should rest for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.24,0:09:45.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see. But I'm afraid that\Nthat's out of the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.95,0:09:48.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am fine. I shall\Nsee to the drive...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.87,0:09:50.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milady...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.83,0:09:52.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That reminds me, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.58,0:09:57.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is technically\Nprivileged information, but here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.25,0:09:59.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.21,0:10:02.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A patient file. Lt. Marito's.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.55,0:10:03.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Patient file?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.17,0:10:08.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's also a prescription.\NFor you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.26,0:10:10.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.19,0:10:18.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.07,0:10:24.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Compared to where I've been sleeping\Nuntil now, this is paradise.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.83,0:10:40.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Aldnoah drive online.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.13,0:10:43.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We have power!\NWe're good to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.46,0:10:45.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Deucalion, lift off.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.47,0:10:53.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That girl's father tried to kill\Nthe princess, a fellow Martian.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.81,0:10:57.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Martians killed her father,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.19,0:11:02.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and then that Rayet girl turned a gun on the\Nprincess even though she's a Martian, too.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.94,0:11:08.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And I... killed my own\Nbest friend.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.57,0:11:16.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What was it like to be shot\Nby a friend, Humeray?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.39,0:11:34.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Slaine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.85,0:11:45.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is our data on Tanegashima, the\Nisland where you were retrieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.44,0:11:48.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,An enormous dock\Nand shipbuilding facilities...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.53,0:11:50.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You saw a ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.61,0:11:51.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.95,0:11:54.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And that ship was Aldnoah-equipped?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.62,0:11:56.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.24,0:12:00.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And was it Princess Asseylum\Nwho activated that Aldnoah?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.75,0:12:05.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You hold your tongue out\Nof concern for her?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.59,0:12:08.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you familiar with this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.55,0:12:11.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.76,0:12:13.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Deucalion.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.55,0:12:16.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A Kataphrakt belonging\Nto Viscountess Orlane
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.10,0:12:18.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,that has gravity\Ncontrol capability.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.85,0:12:20.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Viscountess Orlane?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.02,0:12:23.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The woman who was\Nto be my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.98,0:12:27.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We did our very utmost.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.15,0:12:32.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Using the power of the Aldnoah that His Majesty\Nbestowed upon us, we ruled the people,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.11,0:12:34.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,cultivated the wastelands of Vers,\Nexpanded our domain,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.41,0:12:37.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and tried to amass wealth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.41,0:12:42.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But no matter what we did, we would\Nalways be limited by something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.62,0:12:43.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Limited?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.00,0:12:46.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,By water and air.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.05,0:12:50.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In the time of the people of the ancient\Ncivilization that created Aldnoah,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.34,0:12:52.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,water and air\Nwere yet plentiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.34,0:12:57.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But all Vers has now is an atmosphere\Nthat is nearly a vacuum
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.14,0:12:59.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and what little water\Nremains underground.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.97,0:13:04.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, owing to that thin atmosphere,\NVers is constantly buffeted by storms.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.73,0:13:08.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As it stands, no matter how much land there is,\Nthe harvest it yields will always be meager.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.69,0:13:10.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The more our population grows,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.57,0:13:13.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,production always falls short of demand,\Nand we grow ever more impoverished.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.70,0:13:18.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was always a fool's errand\Nto live on that world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.00,0:13:27.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But our second emperor, Emperor Gillzeria,\Nwas a believer in Aldnoah's power
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.67,0:13:31.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and focused all his efforts on developing\Nour industrial capacity.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.01,0:13:36.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The royal family, the masters of\NAldnoah, ruled with an iron fist
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.64,0:13:40.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and turned a deaf ear to the pleas\Nof our suffering people.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.93,0:13:45.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And then... the rising discontent of the\Npopulace was directed against Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.65,0:13:50.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He whipped the people of Vers into\Na frenzy, saying that it was Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.57,0:13:54.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,with their claims of sovereignty,\Nobstruction of independence,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.40,0:13:57.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and attempts to rule us\Nfrom their distant world,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.53,0:14:00.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,that was their enemy and\Nthe source of their suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.12,0:14:05.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Horrifyingly, those lies\Nwere supported by all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.67,0:14:08.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They were the superior race,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.34,0:14:12.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and the filthy subhumans who hoarded Earth's\Nbounty for themselves were evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.21,0:14:15.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Planning to invade Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.76,0:14:19.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we passed through the Hyper Gate\Nand gathered our forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.39,0:14:23.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Foolishly thinking all the while\Nthat our actions were just.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.35,0:14:28.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And then, my Dioscuria, with its\Nsuperior flight capabilities,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.69,0:14:32.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and Orlane's Deucalion went down to\NTanegashima as an advance party.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.91,0:14:41.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How unimpressive...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.95,0:14:45.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This was hardly worth steeling our\Nresolve and coming down for.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.54,0:14:48.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you not agree,\NMilord Saazbaum?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.08,0:14:52.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed. This is quite\Na disappointment, Orlane.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.59,0:14:56.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We will be able to take this planet\Nfar more easily than we expected.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.84,0:15:00.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Our people will be most pleased,\Nto say nothing of His Majesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.52,0:15:07.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.81,0:15:13.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Powerful space-time\Ndistortion waves?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.53,0:15:14.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Hyper Gate!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.86,0:15:20.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Moon... has shattered?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.45,0:15:22.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We're withdrawing, Orlane!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.62,0:15:26.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What's the matter? Withdraw at once!\NThe surface is unsafe!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.33,0:15:30.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The distortions are affecting\Nmy antigravity device!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.88,0:15:32.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can't fly!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.00,0:15:33.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm coming to assist!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.29,0:15:37.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't! It is too late!\NLeave me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.26,0:15:38.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.59,0:15:42.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Orlane!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.19,0:15:59.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will have my revenge for Orlane,\Nmark my words.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.36,0:16:00.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Count!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.24,0:16:03.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Count Saazbaum!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.37,0:16:16.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the battleship Deucalion.\NHQ, requesting docking clearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.96,0:16:19.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Welcome, Deucalion.\NClearance granted.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.05,0:16:22.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Set down in Dock #6.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.47,0:16:24.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Deucalion, acknowledged.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.06,0:16:27.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see it with my own two eyes,\Nand I still can't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.93,0:16:32.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A flying battleship... It's like something\Nout of those Japanese comic books.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.35,0:16:36.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I heard it was abandoned because\Nthey couldn't activate its Aldnoah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.78,0:16:40.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Those reports that they're harboring\NPrincess Asseylum must be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.11,0:16:43.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We finally made it...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.49,0:16:44.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.62,0:16:46.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,United Earth Headquarters...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.02,0:17:23.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Touchdown in 3... 2... 1...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.20,0:17:26.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ship is down.\NNow mooring.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.74,0:17:32.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose this means our\Nvoyage is over, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.08,0:17:34.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.37,0:17:35.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For now, ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.67,0:17:40.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we keep the ship,\Nwhat will the enemy do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.76,0:17:48.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now that we're here,\Nwe're safe, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.81,0:17:50.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is a secret base\N600 meters underground
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.77,0:17:53.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,that was designed to withstand\Na nuclear strike.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.81,0:17:58.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They say that lots of refugees are being\Nhoused in the massive shelters here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.52,0:18:02.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At capacity, they're supposed to have\N3 years' worth of supplies stockpiled.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.07,0:18:04.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But apparently, the numbers\Ndon't add up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.95,0:18:07.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are they over capacity?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.49,0:18:11.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The opposite, apparently.\NThey have too many provisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.50,0:18:16.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like most of the refugees\Nnever made it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.42,0:18:22.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If this place is destroyed...\NTerrans might go extinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.42,0:18:23.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's huge!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.59,0:18:25.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Inaho.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.05,0:18:27.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I looked around.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.14,0:18:32.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's lots of Areions sitting around, so\Nwhy would you keep using that Sleipnir?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.85,0:18:34.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm used to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.23,0:18:35.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's all?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.14,0:18:39.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Heavier armor wouldn't have helped\Nagainst anything we've fought so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.94,0:18:42.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you're okay with it,\Nsuit yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.36,0:18:46.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do we even have to fight now? We can\Nlet the professionals do their job.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.61,0:18:47.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.43,0:18:48.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.45,0:18:50.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be too careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.83,0:18:55.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's got conformal\Npower assist, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.29,0:19:03.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Aldnoah...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.76,0:19:06.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is what started it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.72,0:19:09.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much, Inaho.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.39,0:19:14.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm given to understand that it's\Nyou whom I owe my life to.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.47,0:19:17.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's because\Nwe're in a war.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.02,0:19:21.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How many times\Ndoes this make it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.11,0:19:24.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure. And I wouldn't\Nsay that I've saved it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.78,0:19:27.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is a war, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.20,0:19:31.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're a kind person, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.37,0:19:33.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.08,0:19:39.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After all this is over...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.12,0:19:42.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We will remain friends\Nafter all this is over, won't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.42,0:19:45.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.59,0:19:47.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.63,0:19:51.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milady, it's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.76,0:19:52.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.64,0:19:56.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's be off, Eddelrittuo.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.81,0:19:59.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you'll excuse us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.98,0:20:08.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am Asseylum Vers Allusia.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.45,0:20:11.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am the Princess Royal,\Ngranddaughter of
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.91,0:20:15.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rayregalia Vers Rayvers,\NEmperor of Vers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.37,0:20:18.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I address the people\Nof Father Vers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.75,0:20:22.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I call for an immediate cessation of\Nhostilities in this meaningless war.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.33,0:20:24.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am safe.\NAlive and well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.34,0:20:28.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is not Terrans who made\Nan attempt on my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.22,0:20:32.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was a plot by the Orbital Knights, who have\Ntheir sights set on an invasion of Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.80,0:20:34.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Terrans are innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.22,0:20:38.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stop the fighting immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.43,0:20:40.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And then make peace\Nwith Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.52,0:20:45.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I beg you, put a stop\Nto this tragedy.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.36,0:20:54.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the Tharsis!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.66,0:20:57.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I retrieved it\Nfrom Castle Cruhteo.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.33,0:21:00.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He was unworthy of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.42,0:21:05.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Its Aldnoah drive\Nis powered down...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.17,0:21:08.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Which means that\NCount Cruhteo truly is...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.38,0:21:11.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Asseylum's location\Nhas been pinpointed
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.34,0:21:13.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,via laser transmission\Nto the Moon base.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.89,0:21:18.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Moon base is under the control\Nof those who feel as I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.52,0:21:22.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Her Highness' proclamation\Nwill reach no one's ears.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.94,0:21:26.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The final battle is about to take place\Nat the enemy's main stronghold.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.02,0:21:29.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even with the full might of a Landing\NCastle, it will be no easy feat.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.95,0:21:35.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My debt to your father\Nis paid.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.16,0:21:40.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You may join my forces\Nor you may flee to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.95,0:21:43.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do as you will.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.13,0:21:50.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milord Saazbaum, all launch\Npreparations are now complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.72,0:21:56.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Begin Landing Castle descent!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.09,0:22:01.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Destination: UE Headquarters!\NNovostal'sk, Russia!
